chapter 9
Now we know how an object is born, 
but how long does an object live?
An object’5 life depends entirely on the life of references 
referring to it. If the reference is considered “alive”, the 
object is still alive on the Heap. If the reference dies 
(and we’11 look at what that means in just a moment), the 
object will die. 
50 if an object’5 life depends on the reference 
variable’5 life, how long does a variable live?
That depends on whether the variable is a local variable 
or an instance variable. The code below shows the life of a 
local variable. In the example, the variable is a primitive, 
but variable lifetime is the same whether it’5 a primitive or 
reference variable.
sleep()
read() 5
public class TestLifeOne {
 public void read() {
 int 5 = 42;
 sleep();
 }
 public void sleep() {
 5 = 7;
 }
}
A local variable lives only 
within the method that 
declared the variable.
Variable ‘5’ can be used only within the 
read() method. In other words, the variable 
is in scope only within its own method. No 
other code in the class (or any other class) 
can see ‘5’.
1
2
‘5’ is scoped to the read() 
method, 50 it can’t be used 
anywhere else
An instance variable lives 
as long as the object 
does. If the object is still 
alive, 50 are its instance 
variables.
public void read() {
 int 5 = 42;
 // ‘5’ can be used only
 // within this method.
 // When this method ends,
 // ‘5’ disappears completely.
}
public class Life {
 int size;
 public void setSize(int 5) {
 size = 5;
 // ‘5’ disappears at the 
 // end of this method,
 // but ‘size’ can be used
 // anywhere in the class
 }
}
Variable ‘5’ (this time a method parameter) 
is in scope only within the setSize() 
method. But instance variable size is 
scoped to the life of the object as opposed 
to the life of the method.
BAD!! Not legal to 
use ‘5’ here!
The variable ‘5’ is alive, but in scope only within the 
read() method. When sleep() completes and read() is 
on top of the Stack and running again, read() can 
still see ‘5’. When read() completes and is popped off 
the Stack, ‘5’ is dead. Pushing up digital daisies.
sleep() can’t see the ‘5’ variable. Since 
it’5 not in sleep()’5 own Stack frame, 
sleep() doesn’t know anything about it.
