“We’ve run the simulation four times, and the main module’5 temperature consistently 
drifts out of nominal towards cold”, Sarah said, exasperated. “We installed the new temp-bots last 
week. The readings on the radiator bots, designed to cool the living quarters, seem to be within 
spec, 50 we’ve focused our analysis on the heat retention bots, the bots that help to warm the quar-
ters.” Tom sighed, at first it had seemed that nano-technology was going to really put them ahead 
of schedule. Now, with only five weeks left until launch, some of the orbiter’5 key life support 
systems were still not passing the simulation gauntlet.

“What ratios are you simulating?”, Tom asked. 

“Well if 1 see where you’re going, we already thought of that”, Sarah replied. “Mission 
control will not sign off on critical systems if we run them out of spec. We are required 
to run the v3 radiator bot’5 SimUnits in a 2:1 ratio with the v2 radiator’5 SimUnits”, 
Sarah continued. “Overall, the ratio of retention bots to radiator bots is supposed to 
